Claude’s Plan
Diagramatix — Implementation Plan
Context
Paul Nash and Greg Nash (conversation in Product Creation using Claude.vtt) want to build Diagramatix, a web-based process diagramming tool aimed at business analysts. It is positioned as a smarter, cheaper alternative to Visio, Magic Draw UML, Enterprise Architect, and Lucidchart. The product focuses on superior connector routing, proper BPMN standards compliance, and configurability. This is a greenfield project — no code exists yet.

Technology Stack
Layer	Technology
Framework	Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript
Styling	Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
Diagram Canvas	SVG (rendered inside React, event-driven)
Database	PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM
Auth	Auth.js v5 (credentials / email+password)
Deployment	Vercel (or any Node host)
