1.8 Connector Routing (src/lib/diagram/routing.ts)
MVP: orthogonal routing (right-angle paths)

Input: source element bounds, target element bounds, all other element bounds
Output: array of Point[] waypoints
Algorithm: Manhattan routing with obstacle avoidance
Two routing modes:
Sequence (type: "sequence"): route around all elements (never pass through)
Message (type: "message"): straight line, ignores obstacles (dashed)
On element move: recompute waypoints for all connected connectors
