Key Design Decisions
Diagram data stored as JSON in the Diagram.data field — avoids complex relational queries for the diagram graph; entire diagram loads in one query.
Client-side state managed with useReducer + Context (no extra state library for MVP) — keeps the canvas rendering fast and avoids over-engineering.
Connector routing is pure functional (routing.ts) — given element positions and bounds, deterministically returns waypoints. Makes it easy to test and iterate.
SVG over Canvas — React renders SVG elements directly into the DOM, so drag/click event handling is per-element and idiomatic. No custom hit-testing needed.
No existing BPMN libraries (as explicitly rejected in the design discussion) — full custom implementation for maximum control over rendering and routing behavior.
Verification / Testing Plan
Auth flow: Register → login → protected dashboard accessible → logout → redirect to login
Create diagram: Dashboard → "New Diagram" → select "Basic" type → enter name → redirected to editor
Add elements: Drag rectangle from palette → drops on canvas at cursor position
Move elements: Click element → drag → element moves, canvas re-renders
Connect elements: Hover element → click connection point → drag to second element → connector appears with orthogonal routing
Label editing: Double-click element → type label → click away → label saved
Persist: Refresh page → diagram loads with same elements, positions, connectors
Export: Click Export SVG → .svg file downloads with current diagram contents

