## Project Overview
Web-based BPMN/process diagramming tool built for Paul Nash and Greg Nash.
See transcript: `c:\Git\Diagramatix\Product Creation using Claude.vtt`

## App Location
`c:\Git\Diagramatix\diagramatix\` — Next.js 15/16 app (no `src/` prefix, `app/` at root)

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16.1.6 + TypeScript (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **Database**: PostgreSQL + Prisma 7 (via `@prisma/adapter-pg`)
- **Auth**: Auth.js v5 beta (next-auth@beta), JWT strategy, email+password
- **Canvas**: SVG-based, custom implementation (no bpmn-js)
- Node.js: v24.14.0 at `/c/Program Files/nodejs/` — not on default PATH, use `export PATH="$PATH:/c/Program Files/nodejs"`

## Critical Prisma 7 Differences
- Schema `datasource` has NO `url` field (Prisma 7 breaking change)
- URL passed via `PrismaPg` adapter in `app/lib/db.ts`
- Generated client is at `app/generated/prisma/client` (NOT `app/generated/prisma`)
- JSON fields need `as any` cast for writes; `as unknown as T` for reads

## Next.js 16 Differences
- `middleware.ts` → `proxy.ts` (must export `proxy` named function)
- Auth proxy uses `auth.config.ts` (no Prisma) to avoid Edge runtime issue
- Full auth with Prisma in `auth.ts`

## Key Files
- `app/lib/diagram/types.ts` — all TypeScript types
- `app/lib/diagram/routing.ts` — orthogonal connector routing
- `app/lib/diagram/symbols/definitions.ts` — symbol definitions per diagram type
- `app/hooks/useDiagram.ts` — useReducer-based diagram state
- `app/components/canvas/Canvas.tsx` — SVG canvas (pan/zoom/drop)
- `app/components/canvas/SymbolRenderer.tsx` — per-symbol SVG shapes
- `app/components/canvas/ConnectorRenderer.tsx` — connector paths + arrows
- `app/components/canvas/Palette.tsx` — drag-from palette
- `app/components/canvas/PropertiesPanel.tsx` — right-side properties
- `app/(dashboard)/diagram/[id]/DiagramEditor.tsx` — editor shell + auto-save

